					<p>While analyzing the book <em>La nuit sera blanche: Barthes, „La Chambre claire”, le cinéma </em>by Jean Narboni, author focused on the question of photography in Roland Barthes' oeuvre, especially in his late or even never completed works. He also writes about Barthes' planned seminar on photographies of prototypes of the Proustian figures.</p>
